caption: Loved the sound and the atmosphere. Our waiter was so friendly and accommodating. Hideaway is perfectly named because the aesthetic, feel and location. Highly recommend and will certainly be back.
Amazing service, fantastic food and atmosphere. Highly recommend the buffalo poutine!
We went on a Friday.  We were seated in 15 minutes, no reservation.  Food was quick and delicious.  Wait staff gave us the perfect amount of attention!

Apps and drinks are awesome, especially the cured meats & fries. Max, the owner, is great & catered to all of my dietary restrictions. Drinks were served by Megan- who was so kind and fun. We love it here and will definitely be going back soon.
This is my new fave place for burgers in the Park Ave area. Also I love the pretzel appetizer. The service here is always great
Awesome restaurant, we went there for brunch on 10/25/20 and everything was great!
Great place for burgers and fries. Speedy service and very hospitable. Ask for Jon, he’s the guy who took care of me. He knows his stuff and is a genius when it comes to beer knowledge.
Great service and delicious food.  Generous proportions.

We used the Hideway for catering our sons wedding and rehearsal. The food was amazing and Max and the wait staff were so accommodating and flexible. Definitely would use them again and highly recommend them! Thank you for all you did!
LOVED IT!
Very Welcoming, great appetizers in time of Covid. Preboxed.
Loved the three-course dinner tonight!  Excellent food!
Bland food, terrible margarita.

We had a 21st birthday party at The Hideaway and it was phenomenal! The food, the service and the atmosphere were top notch. I booked the event with the owner who was professional and friendly. He was quick to respond to any of my questions and helped me to figure out a menu that fit our guests tastes perfectly. The servers were also so genuinely friendly and quick to accommodate our requests. I can't say enough about our experience. Thank you for a great experience!

Wow. Where do I start? We had 11:30am reservations. We were seated immediately. It took a while to get our drinks. After about 35 minutes someone FINALLY took our food orders and then almost 45 minutes later we had our meals, after numerous mentions to our waiter. My husbands medium rare burger came back completely well done. He didn’t want to bother sending it back because who knows how long it would take to get a new one. My pancakes were blah and they gave very little syrup with them (there were 3 fairly large ones.)   We really wanted to like it here, but I just can’t recommend it. Service was terrible and the food was mediocre at best. Too many other places on or near Park Ave to enjoy.
Delicious food! beer selection not the best, but good choice of local beer.
Maitre'd was initially un responsive but later improved, my beer was available (BIG plus-Miller high life) food wad good,service was great 👍👍

My husband and I used The Hideaway to cater our wedding. We weren’t sure who to go with but we had just gone to a friends wedding who used The Hideaway and we were so impressed! Max was phenomenal to work with. Although I did not end up having a chance to eat at my wedding, my guests kept telling me how great the food was. The hand passed appetizers, and meat and cheese board served during cocktail hour were said to be amazing. Through the whole planning process Max was so professional and kind, always making sure any questions were answered and any needs met. I also wanted mini pies done for the wedding and Max and his chef came together to come up with what we wanted and they turned out awesome! I would definitely recommend their service!
Great atmosphere and great food!

Unfortunately I can not give 0 stars. I never received my food after over 2 hours of being there. The server clearly can't do his job. I also told the bar tender who was literally standing next to the guy making sushi. And still didn't get my food. I've never been somewhere and not received my food. Chain restaurants have better service. Never have I experienced such terrible service and u  deserve nothing less than a scathing review. Don't go here

Our reservations  for 4 adults were December 11,2019 at 6 PM.  When I called earlier in the day the person on the phone was helpful re: questions I had. However, on arrival the first person I encountered at the bar seemed very disinterested and referred me to 3 girls nearby who were engaged in conversation and finally one of them escorted us to a table in the center of the restaurant area which was not an area I had requested.  Nearby was a table of 3 persons who were engaged in very loud conversation.  We requested a change in table to a quieter one at the end of the seating area. The noise from said table was still extremely loud and distracting for anyone trying to have a normal conversation.  The acoustics are nonexistent.  We we're with friends from the Netherlands and the atmosphere did not make a good impression.  The waiter was friendly but also loud.  The food was excellent and we were pleased with our choices but the noise interfered with our conversation.  Bread was not included and we paid $2 for a very small loaf of bread.  Two persons in our party order Irish Coffee which as presented in a coffee cup.  When we commented on this presentation the waiter remarked this was the way the owner made it.  It was also over priced $10 per cup.  In spite of the food being good I would not recommend this restaurant due to the many issues mentioned above and would not plan on returning again.

Max Gordon from Hideway catered our daughter's wedding. The dinner was exceptional. Does not matter if the order was steak, chicken, salmon or vegetarian. Each meal was prepared to a perfection, with right flavor and presentation. It was very satisfying to see Max around making sure our guests were happy with the food of their choice. Max and his team contributed to a perfect dinner for our daughter's wedding. It will be memorable to all of us. Max is a young professional, with a lot of potential for a successful future in this field. He is very welcoming, listens to the customer's needs and delivers his promise. I would always recommend his business for any type of event and I have no doubt in his performance. Thank you Max.

I ordered to go, and everything was delicious.  The Seared Tuna wrap was Devine. The fries were good also. Greedy as I am, I wanted more, but they gave the perfect amount complete with ketchup.  It was a great meal well worth the price. There were no issues with pick up nor in using gift certificates. Looking forward to eating inside next time. Parking is a bit confusing, so heads up if you are driving there and staying to eat.
Clean friendly beautiful ambience

We went for mothers day. Had reservations for 10:30. Got seated quickly, drink orders came fast as well, but from there it went downhill. Our food didnt come until 11:45. The server rarely checked on us, and when she finally did bring our food never asked if we needed refills. When I was finally able to flag her down, it took until I was done with my food to get my refill. When she refilled my coffee she completely ignored the rest of the tables need for refills and needed to be flagged down again. The seating was atrocious and the staff was poorly managed. At least the food was good, after they finally brought out certain items they forgot and needed to be reminded of. Only getting 2 stars because the food was good and the price matched.

Staff and food were great.
Excellent service, great atmosphere, the food is delicious and the prices are accurate for the setting/quality.
New menu is quite limited. Hamburg was generous and flavorful

Great place with great device & delicious foods
The staff here is excellent and the food is fresh and delicious. I highly recommend ordering the shrimp and scallop risotto. Last meal worthy.
Great food & service.
Good food.  Innovative drinks.  Pleasant surroundings.

A Rochester gem! 5 stars⭐️ Excellent food & service. Cozy and warm atmosphere.  Owner is experienced and on site. Chef is from well known Rochester eateries. Prices are very reasonable. Thank you for our great meal.
Everything was slow. Took some time to place order, receive it and get check. Menu was limited, but food was excellent
I had eaten here a few weeks ago and loved it. I brought my family this time. Both my girls like to eat vegan and they have great choices for that. All our meals were fantastic. Highly recommend!
Absolutely love this restaurant! Excellent neighborhood, the inside is well decorated. Our server was phenomenal! Definately coming back!
Food was phenomenal, service was great and drinks were delicious! Definitely a great place to eat! We will definitely come back!
Amazing menu and food, yummy cocktails, beautiful presentation, and great service every time! This is becoming my go to restaurant!

Our waitress Kate too 15 minutes to come to our table, when there was no other customers except at the bar. A table came in about the time she finally showed up, and she served them first instead of us. The food took a bit which honestly isn't the problem, I work in food, I understand. It's when she brought me my food and told me they don't have the fruit to go with it. Which wouldn't have been a big deal if she had offered something as compensation, but she didn't. Then I asked why I didn't get the side of home fries, and she said it doesn't come with it. She said it was stated in the menu, but it only said pasta and pancakes don't come with home fries. And you could make the argument that french toast is in the same family as pancakes, but I think it should be clearly stated in the menu like she said it was. Everytime she came over  I could see the attitude in her body language, which is extremely unprofessional, especially in our line of work dealing with the public. At least the food was good, but overpriced...$10 for 2 pieces of French toast and in her words, "just a small bowl of blueberries"....would not recommend
Our experience was great. The food was very delicious!!!! The hostess was very personable. Our waitress Lisa was exceptional. We will definitely be back.

Food was good. Major complaint is that we were sat towards the back because the dining room was loud due to there being a party at the bar. We weren't warned before hand that the dining area in the back was unpleasantly hot. The waitress opened windows after commenting on how hot it was but that didn't help much given the fact that it was 90 outside. A little disappointed in the dining experience, food was good though.
1st time here it was Great Food!
Always amazing food and service. Glad to have it as a part of the neighborhood. A little on the expensive side but the good is definitely worth it.
over priced for what it is but good food!

I ordered on grub hub. One of the menu items I ordered was not yet part of the menu. Grubhub posted it by mistake. I don't blame the restaurant for that. I do blame them for refunding part of the order without telling me and not giving me a chance to cancel the whole order. 1 of us got food. 1 of us didn't and we weren't told ahead of time

I liked the vibe here. It was a fun, relaxed atmosphere while still having class. Not sloppy. Very Park Ave. The cocktail menu was well laid out, I like how they did that (picture included). I got the Texas Punch and it was fabulous. I will literally be going back just for that. There's something for everyone, the menu is extensive.  Didn't get anything to eat, just drinks. They IDd everyone, very play-book. We sat at the bar by the window overlooking the street.
